Purpose and third-party notices

This repository is published for educational and interoperability research
purposes only. It documents the USB Audio Class behavior and proprietary
control-transfer protocol of the Elgato Wave:3, a device I physically own, and
provides an independent open-source Linux control daemon.

No proprietary Elgato firmware, driver binaries, or copyrighted source code are
distributed in this repository. The Elgato Wave Link installer packages
(`.msix`, `.dmg`) and their extracted binary contents have been removed; only
independent research notes, string/path summaries, and file manifests are
retained.

Elgato®, Wave:3®, Wave Link®, Corsair®, and related trademarks are the property
of Corsair Memory, Inc. / Elgato and are used here solely for identification
and commentary under nominative fair use. This project is not affiliated with,
endorsed by, or sponsored by Corsair Memory, Inc., Elgato, or their respective
affiliates.

The `native-linux/` implementation is licensed under the MIT License above.
The vendored upstream `wave3ctl` kernel module and Python CLI under
`native-linux/wave3ctl/` retain their original license.
